-- GP Investments Plans to Sell Stake in Health Insurer Tempo, Valor Reports
-- B y   T e l m a   M a r o t t o
-- 2010-10-15T11:26:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-15/gp-investments-plans-to-sell-stake-in-health-insurer-tempo-valor-reports.html
Tempo Assist, a health-care
insurance company whose biggest investor is GP Investments Ltd.,
hired UBS AG to find a buyer, Valor Economico newspaper
reported, citing people close to the deal it didn’t identify.  The deal may be worth about 900 million reais ($542
million), the Sao Paulo-based newspaper reported. Tempo Assist
is the brand name of Tempo Participacoes SA.  At least six companies showed interest in the deal, Valor
said. Amil Participacoes SA, the insurance unit of Banco
Bradesco SA, Mapfre SA, Sul America SA, health insurance
brokerage Qualicorp Group and UnitedHealth Group Inc. assessed
Tempo’s information, Valor said.  Marcia Schuler, an outside spokeswoman for Tempo with
MSchuler & Associados Comunicação Empresarial, said the company
doesn’t comment on market speculation when contacted by
Bloomberg News today.  Tempo, Amil, Bradesco Saude and Sul America told Valor they
don’t comment on market speculation. Qualicorp denied it’s
taking part in the transaction, Valor said. UnitedHealth and
Mapfre didn’t answer Valor’s requests, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
